                  </hi>. I am the prisoner's father—I am a smith and bell<lb></lb>hanger, and live at No. 19. Houndsditch. I did not send my son to Mr. Verry for any razors on the 10th of March—I had not seen him for a fort<lb></lb>night before—he is an apprentice to Mr. Clive, a printer. on Bread-street-hill.</p>
